title: Bindi Irwin Celebrates Australia Day With an Adorable Koala – See the Pic!
text: Bindi Irwin Celebrates Australia Day With an Adorable Koala – See the Pic! by Raphael Chestang 6:23   Photo: Getty Images Bindi Irwin is having a cute and cuddly Australia Day, judging by a recent Instagram post. The Dancing With the Stars champ, 18, shared a photo of herself with a furry koala on Wednesday in celebration of her country's official national holiday. A photo posted by Bindi Irwin (@bindisueirwin) on Jan 25, 2017 at 11:56am PST "Australia Zoo will always be my home," she wrote in the caption. "Happy Australia Day, lovelies." Irwin is back at the zoo (which was founded by her grandparents, Bob and Lyn Irwin, in 1970) after ringing in the new year with her boyfriend, Chandler Powell, in Tasmania. WATCH: Bindi Irwin Channels Her Late Father During Crocodile Feeding at Australia Zoo The zoo is currently owned by Bindi's mom, Terri, and features many amazing creatures, including crocodiles, tortoises and lemurs. It is also the location where Irwin and Powell, 20, first met in November 2013. They have been dating long-distance ever since as he continues his wakeboarding career in the U.S.
